---
description: Always implement and verify web (desktop) and mobile layouts together
globs: **/*
alwaysApply: true
---

When changing UI, layout, banners, navigation, or pages:

- Design and test for **mobile (≤1023px)** and **desktop (≥1024px)** in the same change.
- Prefer responsive CSS (grid/flex breakpoints) over separate hacks.
- Avoid horizontal-only patterns on mobile unless scroll is obvious; use 2-column grids when items are small (e.g. 234×60 banners).
- Check touch targets, safe areas, fixed bottom nav padding, and `overflow` clipping on small screens.
- Ensure static assets under `public/` exist for both environments (run `npm run predev` / ensure scripts if needed).
